@node 001
About PLone

     PLone (PlayLister One) is a PlayList AddOn for the Hippoplayer/Play16 GUI
     Replace program PlayGui of Richard Kapp.
     The function of PLone consists of storing current modules of PlayGui to
     taking over and this into a list.  From this list the user can select then
     a module to begin without arranging only PlayGui to it a Filerequester to
     open (and thus the long travels to the file.)

     PLone uses Pictures, which are called in this connection 'Skin' for the
     GUI. These Pics can be supposed and changed by the user. Some Skins are
     already contained.

Feature:

     - Skinsupport
     - simple operation
     - can be used also without PlayGui (reduced)
     - data alterable (titles, comment, Composer and path)
     - modules can be taken over from PlayGui directly or over a Filerequester.
     - exporting the list as HippoPlayer, DeliTracker, EgalePlayer2 Playlist
     - Load HippoPlayer/DeliTracker Playlists

       PLone is Freeware
@endnode

@node 002

     PLone runs on each Amiga with sufficient memory; *)

     Software:

     PlayGui 3.0+
     some Datatypes
     HippoPlayer
     Play16
     mpega
     gmplay

     rexxmast (optionally)
@endnode
