@node 004_1
The use of PLone takes place by means of the 3 items of the window and the
Menue's.

The 3 items of the window are:

.--.------------------------------------------.--.--.
|--| PLone x.x                                |  |  |
|---------------------------------------------'--'--|
|  .---------------------------------------------.  |
|  |    1. Item = Listview                       |  |
|  |                                             |  |
|  |                                             |  |
|  |                                             |  |
|  |                                             |  |
|  |                                             |  |
|  |                                             |  |
|  |                                             |  |
|  |                                             |  |
|  `---------------------------------------------'  |
|  .---------------------. .---------------------.  |
|  | 2. Item = Buttons1  | | 3. item = Buttons2  |  |
|  `---------------------' `---------------------'  |
`---------------------------------------------------'


1.  Item = the Listview:  Here are the entries

2.  Item = Listview Buttons:  Hereby the entries of the Listviews are
           moved to the left/right

3.  Item = option Buttons:  Here the functions are accommodated such as
           ADDS or Play

The menu functions are explained in Menue's.
The Buttons is explained in Buttons

@endnode

@node 004_2

In the following now the Menue's is explained by PLone:

  Main:
  -----
       New Skin
       ---------
        Load a new Skin
        

       Hide/Show Gadgets
       ------------------
        Hide/Show the Gadgets


       PlayerControl
       --------------
        open the PlayerControl (PlayerCTRL) Window


       Settings
       ---------
        Open the Settings WIndow


       About
       ------
           PLone - PLone Infos
        The Skin - Display the skin.txt


       Quit
       -----
        Quit PLone


  Edit:
  -----
       Add File
       ---------
        Add one or more files into the List


       Add Directory
       --------------
        add a Directory into the List

 
       Add Line
       ---------
        add a Line into the current Position


  Sort:
  -----
       Title, comment, composer, path
       -------------------------------
        Sort the List


  Data:
  -----
       Clear
       ------
        Clear the List


       Load
       -----
        Load a new PLone Playlist.


       Save
       -----
        Save the List (s:plone.data)


       Save as
       --------
        Open a Filerequester and save the List


       Import Playlist
       ----------------
        Load Hippoplayer/DeliTracker PlayLists


       Export
       -------
        Hippoplayer - Save the List as a Hippoplayer 2.44+ Playlist.

        DeliTracker - Save the List as a DeliTracker II Playlist.

        EaglePlayer - Save the List as a Eagleplayer2/Pysion List.

        Ascii       - (not finished)
                      Save the List as a Ascii file

@endnode

@node 004_3

     There are 2 types of Buttons:  The Listview and the Functionbuttons.

     ListView Buttons:  Induce contents after ListView's left/on the right
                        around all data to display.
                        These are the 5 Buttons left in the window.

                   .----.----.----.----.----.
                   | << | <  | <> |  > | >> |
                   `----`----`----`----`----'

     Functions (from on the left of to the right)

     << - list is moved to the left 5 steps
      < - list moved around one walked to the left
     <> - one branches again to the at the beginning of the list
      > - 1 walked to the right
     >> - 5 steps to the right



Function Buttons: here the ADD or Play Buttons. The Functionbuttons are the
                  5 on the right Side

                   .----.----.----.----.----.
                   |add |Play|Edit|Del |Save|
                   `----`----`----`----`----'

     Functions (from left to the right)

     ADD - as current module adds or SAMPLE, the PlayGui even plays into the
           list.
           PlayGui is opens not actively a Filerequester to selects of files.
           @{"READ THIS" link 000_0}!

    Play - transfers the Selected module/Sample to PlayGui.
           Afterwards still the Play Button must be pressed with PlayGui.

    Edit - a window opens in which one the Title, Composer, COMMENTS and path
           of the current entry modify can.

     Del - deletes the current entry

    Save - Save the list (s:PLone.data)

@endnode

@node 004_4

They can control contents of the Listview's by the keys of the numeric
keyboard:


   7 [Home]  - Jump to the first line

   8  [/\]   - !not yet supported!

   9 [Pg Up] - moves the list of 15 entries upward

   4  [<--]  - moves the list of 5 steps to the left

   5         - Jumps to the left site

   6  [-->]  - moves the list of 5 steps to the right

   1  [End]  - Move to the last entry

   2  [\/]   - !Not yet supported!

   3 [Pg Dn] -  moves the list of 15 entries down


@endnode

@node 004_5

Press HELP to activate the PLone Helpmode (Help is on will displayed)
Now select a function and a little Window whit a short description will
open. The Function is Disabled. Press HELP again to deactivate the Help
Mode.

@endnode

